results.name: Cubes which are the sum of two consecutive primes.
link: Donovan Johnson, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
maple: KD: = proc() local a,b,c;  a: = ithprime(n) + ithprime(n+1); b:= evalf(a^(1/3)); if b=floor(b) then RETURN(a):  fi; end: seq(KD(), n=1..1000000);
program: (PARI) n=0; forstep(j=2, 55778, 2, c=j^3; c2=c/2; if(precprime(c2)+nextprime(c2)==c, n++; write("b226524.txt", n " " c))) /* _Donovan Johnson_, Sep 02 2013 */
xref: Cf. A062703 (analog for squares), A061308 (lesser of the consecutive primes), A071220 (index of that prime), A074925 (a(n)^(1/3)).
